<subSubSection type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Pterochthoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">PTEROCHTHONIIDAE</taxonomicName>
Grandjean, 1950
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
Among the 
<taxonomicName infraOrder="Enarthronota" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" rank="infraOrder">Enarthronota</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Pterochthoniidae" genus="Pterochthonius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angelus">Pterochthonius angelus</taxonomicName>
is remarkable by its exceptional habitus, whilst many of its characters must be regarded as unique and primitive. It is impossible to classify the species in one of the above-mentioned families, so that Grandjean (1950) created a separate family 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Pterochthoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Pterochthoniidae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
